attributes.about_this_biz_history:

In 2011, the brand expanded to the US and mainland China to continue its tradition.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Gather is the residence dining room inside Place Vanier, a first year student residence on the University of British Columbia Vancouver campus. 

Place Vanier is named after Georges Vanier, a distinguished war figure in both World Wars and the first French-Canadian Governor General. Place Vanier first opened in 1959 with the commons block and two houses. By 1968 there were twelve houses. 

Gather serves daily meals to the nearly 1500 students who live in Place Vanier, UBC staff and faculty, and the campus community. In summer, Place Vanier and Gather open as a hostel and accommodation for conference guests.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Globally inspired, locally sourced meals are our passion! Gather serves up fresh, healthy, West Coast contemporary cuisine with global inspiration seven days a week. Where else can you find gourmet burgers, Vij's Indian, Latin American street food, sushi burritos, and a salad bar serving UBC Farm produce all in one place?

Fresh seafood is Ocean Wise™ certified, we serve local and/or organic fruits and vegetables, and our beef burgers and fresh chicken are halal.

Curry fish ball, egg waffles, rice noodle roll, fish soup noodle combo,, tapioca drinks and etc. – You can find all those popular street snacks in Bubble Waffle Cafe. We are located in Aberdeen Centre, Public Market and Public Plaza. The best egg waffle and fish soup noodle combo are here!

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Burgoo came to life because we believe everyone needs a little comfort and a place to enjoy some great comfort food. No matter what the season is, a tiny bit of comfort can go a long way to making someone's day more satisfying.

We felt that creating an old-world, countryside ambience in our locations--through earth tones, natural finishes and materials--would harken back to a simpler time. We hope we've achieved that in some small way and trust that all those who come here experience Burgoo's essence.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Friends since 13 years old, founders Austin and Jackson always grew up dreaming about how they would, one day, start up a business together. Fast forward 10 years in November of 2016, Rice Burger was created! 

We, at Rice Burger, are excited to share with you our take on this Japanese classic!
attributes.about_this_biz_history:
The concept of rice burgers originated from Japan. After its introduction, rice burgers exploded in popularity across Asia as an alternative to traditional hamburgers.

Our ingredients are all locally sourced and prepared with the highest level of quality. We truly believe that good food does not need to break the bank. We, at Rice Burger, are excited to share with you our take on this Japanese classic!

Come sit down and have a burger or some delicious Popcorn Chicken at our new location on 2630 Sassamat. 

Give us a call! It'll be the best choice you've ever made!
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Rice Burger offers an original product that is hand-pressed and made in a unique way. Our taste is signature, our burgers delicious and our self-created popcorn chicken is to be a guaranteed favorite. We stand out because we don't believe that quality food should break the bank. We're offering satisfying, top of the line burgers with a Japanese twist. Customers are attracted to us for our creative products and exceptional customer service. We make it a priority to ensure that our clients are more than satisfied.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Meet our Executive Chef, Jimmy Khinda. Jimmy is a Master of Italian Cuisine.  His experiences include being a Chef for Executive Inn Hotels in BC and spent 3-years in Italy where he became familiar in using local ingredients, spices, preparations and serving techniques used in the country  where it is rich of culture, heritage and tradition.
Jimmy's profession had the fortune and experience of landing him with different Hotels and Restaurants all over the world. Some of his favorite places are Italy, France and the United States.
Jimmy truly has a passion for the culinary arts, henceforth  landing him with his own Restaurant, Bella Roma. A friendly smile welcomes you to Bella Roma. If you wish, ask your server to invite Jimmy to your table to say Hello!

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Best friends Thuy Kelp & Rose Concepcion have shared a passion for creating fresh and delicious food for over a decade.

Since the late eighties, they have gained valuable experience while working in acclaimed kitchens across North America, in 2003, they brought their combine creative passion to Vancouver's West Point Grey Village and opened MIX The Bakery.

This neighbourhood, artisan bakery & cafe have become a comforting meeting place for locals, while providing signature products for the finest restaurants in town.  Thuy and Rose, along with their culinary team, are dedicated to providing Vancouver with unique and tasty delectables, in a wamr and welcome atmosphere!
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
We specialize in our award-winning artisan breads and baked goods.  We have proudly operated our comforting neighbourhood cafe as well as supplied our artisan bread to the city's finest kitchens.

At MIX The Bakery, we use time-honoured techniques, which are balanced with unique flavours and textures.  Our line of hand made breads include varieties from around the world and is individually designed to our high qaulity standards.  No short cuts are taken in our processes, as we believe this yields the freshest and tastiest results.

In addition, we offer creative catering to satisfy any breakfast, lunch, or party get-together.  We have a variety of sandwiches, salads, and sweets in our menu but we welcome any suggestions to create off-menu items for special occasions.

MIX The Bakery also has a line of all-natural artsinal preserves made in house. They are recognized by Vancouver Magazine as one of the Top 101 Things to Taste in BC and can be found in local markets and specialty stores.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Gather is the residence dining room inside Place Vanier, a first year student residence on the University of British Columbia Vancouver campus. 

Place Vanier is named after Georges Vanier, a distinguished war figure in both World Wars and the first French-Canadian Governor General. Place Vanier first opened in 1959 with the commons block and two houses. By 1968 there were twelve houses. 

Gather serves daily meals to the nearly 1500 students who live in Place Vanier, UBC staff and faculty, and the campus community. In summer, Place Vanier and Gather open as a hostel and accommodation for conference guests.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Globally inspired, locally sourced meals are our passion! Gather serves up fresh, healthy, West Coast contemporary cuisine with global inspiration seven days a week. Where else can you find gourmet burgers, Vij's Indian, Latin American street food, sushi burritos, and a salad bar serving UBC Farm produce all in one place?

Fresh seafood is Ocean Wise™ certified, we serve local and/or organic fruits and vegetables, and our beef burgers and fresh chicken are halal.

At Sesame we believe in serving whole, nourishing foods that energize the body.

Our recipes are inspired by favourites of Chinese, Thai and Vietnamese cuisine, and we strive to re-create those authentic flavours in our dishes.

We work hard to serve dynamic flavours made with fresh ingredients on-site, fairly priced and with kindness.

Order online for contactless payment and pickup.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Chef Hung commenced his culinary apprenticeship at the tender age of 17. Throughout his 20 years of culinary experience, he has developed unrivaled techniques and his own secret recipes. He is a three-time champion of the Taipei International Beef Noodle Festival Competition between the years of 2007 to 2010. 

In 2009, under the management of the Fairchild Group, Chef Hung Taiwanese Beef Noodle has evolved into an international chain. Benefitting from the global network of the group, the brand opened its North American flagship location in Richmond, BC. In 2011, the brand expanded to the US and mainland China to continue its tradition.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Burgoo came to life because we believe everyone needs a little comfort and a place to enjoy some great comfort food. No matter what the season is, a tiny bit of comfort can go a long way to making someone's day more satisfying.

We felt that creating an old-world, countryside ambience in our locations--through earth tones, natural finishes and materials--would harken back to a simpler time. We hope we've achieved that in some small way and trust that all those who come here experience Burgoo's essence.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Friends since 13 years old, founders Austin and Jackson always grew up dreaming about how they would, one day, start up a business together. Fast forward 10 years in November of 2016, Rice Burger was created! 

We, at Rice Burger, are excited to share with you our take on this Japanese classic!
attributes.about_this_biz_history:
The concept of rice burgers originated from Japan. After its introduction, rice burgers exploded in popularity across Asia as an alternative to traditional hamburgers.

Our ingredients are all locally sourced and prepared with the highest level of quality. We truly believe that good food does not need to break the bank. We, at Rice Burger, are excited to share with you our take on this Japanese classic!

Come sit down and have a burger or some delicious Popcorn Chicken at our new location on 2630 Sassamat. 

Give us a call! It'll be the best choice you've ever made!
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Rice Burger offers an original product that is hand-pressed and made in a unique way. Our taste is signature, our burgers delicious and our self-created popcorn chicken is to be a guaranteed favorite. We stand out because we don't believe that quality food should break the bank. We're offering satisfying, top of the line burgers with a Japanese twist. Customers are attracted to us for our creative products and exceptional customer service. We make it a priority to ensure that our clients are more than satisfied.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Meet our Executive Chef, Jimmy Khinda. Jimmy is a Master of Italian Cuisine.  His experiences include being a Chef for Executive Inn Hotels in BC and spent 3-years in Italy where he became familiar in using local ingredients, spices, preparations and serving techniques used in the country  where it is rich of culture, heritage and tradition.
Jimmy's profession had the fortune and experience of landing him with different Hotels and Restaurants all over the world. Some of his favorite places are Italy, France and the United States.
Jimmy truly has a passion for the culinary arts, henceforth  landing him with his own Restaurant, Bella Roma. A friendly smile welcomes you to Bella Roma. If you wish, ask your server to invite Jimmy to your table to say Hello!

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Best friends Thuy Kelp & Rose Concepcion have shared a passion for creating fresh and delicious food for over a decade.

Since the late eighties, they have gained valuable experience while working in acclaimed kitchens across North America, in 2003, they brought their combine creative passion to Vancouver's West Point Grey Village and opened MIX The Bakery.

This neighbourhood, artisan bakery & cafe have become a comforting meeting place for locals, while providing signature products for the finest restaurants in town.  Thuy and Rose, along with their culinary team, are dedicated to providing Vancouver with unique and tasty delectables, in a wamr and welcome atmosphere!
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
We specialize in our award-winning artisan breads and baked goods.  We have proudly operated our comforting neighbourhood cafe as well as supplied our artisan bread to the city's finest kitchens.

At MIX The Bakery, we use time-honoured techniques, which are balanced with unique flavours and textures.  Our line of hand made breads include varieties from around the world and is individually designed to our high qaulity standards.  No short cuts are taken in our processes, as we believe this yields the freshest and tastiest results.

In addition, we offer creative catering to satisfy any breakfast, lunch, or party get-together.  We have a variety of sandwiches, salads, and sweets in our menu but we welcome any suggestions to create off-menu items for special occasions.

MIX The Bakery also has a line of all-natural artsinal preserves made in house. They are recognized by Vancouver Magazine as one of the Top 101 Things to Taste in BC and can be found in local markets and specialty stores.
To enhance the natural flavour and ensure the highest degree of quality and minimize cholesterol in all the dishes we prepare, 100% pure vegetable oil is used for all cooking. NO MSG IS USED!

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.
